sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant API as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Operator as TrustyAI Operator<br/>Controller
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Route as Route (Passthrough)
    participant TLSSvc as Service (TLS)<br/>443/TCP → 8443
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PVC as PersistentVolume
    participant KServe as KServe InferenceService
    participant ModelMesh as ModelMesh Pod
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus

    %% Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Creation
    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,PVC: Flow 1: TrustyAI Service Creation
        User->>API: Create TrustyAIService CR<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+<br/>kubeconfig auth
        API->>Operator: CR Watch Notification<br/>Internal
        Operator->>API: Create ServiceAccount<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create ClusterRoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create PVC<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create Deployment<br/>(TrustyAI + OAuth Proxy)<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create Services<br/>(Internal + TLS)<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create ServiceMonitors<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        Operator->>API: Create Route<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
    end

    %% Flow 2: External Metrics Access
    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over User,TrustyAI: Flow 2: External Metrics Access (OAuth)
        User->>Router: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.3
        Router->>Route: Forward<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS1.2+ (passthrough)
        Route->>TLSSvc: Route to service<br/>HTTPS/443
        TLSSvc->>OAuth: Forward to OAuth proxy<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS1.2+
        OAuth->>API: Validate OAuth token<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS1.2+
        API-->>OAuth: Token validated
        OAuth->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 (validated)
        TrustyAI-->>OAuth: Metrics response
        OAuth-->>Router: HTTPS response<br/>TLS1.2+ Bearer Token Cookie
        Router-->>User: Metrics (JSON/Prometheus)
    end

    %% Flow 3: KServe Inference Logging
    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Operator,PVC: Flow 3: KServe Inference Logging
        Operator->>API: Patch InferenceService CR<br/>Add inference logger URL<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        API->>KServe: CR Update Notification
        KServe->>TrustyAI: POST inference payload<br/>HTTP/80 to service
        TrustyAI->>PVC: Store inference data<br/>Filesystem (Pod UID)
    end

    %% Flow 4: ModelMesh Payload Processing
    rect rgb(255, 250, 240)
        Note over Operator,PVC: Flow 4: ModelMesh Payload Processing
        Operator->>API: Patch ModelMesh Deployment<br/>Set MM_PAYLOAD_PROCESSORS env<br/>HTTPS/6443 ServiceAccount Token
        API->>ModelMesh: Deployment Update
        ModelMesh->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>HTTP/80 to service
        TrustyAI->>PVC: Store payload data<br/>Filesystem (Pod UID)
    end

    %% Flow 5: Prometheus Metrics Scraping
    rect rgb(250, 240, 255)
        Note over Prometheus,TrustyAI: Flow 5: Prometheus Metrics Scraping
        Prometheus->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>HTTP/80 via service<br/>ServiceAccount Token (optional)
        TrustyAI-->>Prometheus: Metrics (trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)<br/>HTTP response
    end
